Jargon buster


Overview

Research, buy, and track investments funds via our Global Investment Centre
Our Global Investment Centre is our investments service through which you can open and invest in a Funds portfolio and ISA Funds portfolio, giving you access to investment funds from HSBC and a wide range of other providers.
Why use Global Investment Centre to buy and track your investments?



Choose from an extensive range of funds 
Choose to buy, sell or switch funds either online or by phone
Start investing with £100 into each class of funds shares you choose 
Value your investment in real time, and track its performance online 




Invest in a tax-efficient way through an ISA funds portfolio
Access GIC via your Personal Internet Banking and manage all your accounts in one convenient place
0% initial charge*
0.39% Account Fee when investing in clean share class funds
It’s quick and easy to apply 



*An annual management charge and other expenses will apply

Eligibility criteria

Eligibility requirements




You can apply for Global Investment Centre if you:

are aged 18 or over
are a UK resident with a permanent UK residential address
have an HSBC current and/or savings account





You cannot apply for a Funds Portfolio and ISA Funds Portfolio if you're a non-UK resident (including if you are a UK Crown Servant working overseas).
Accounts cannot be held in joint names and non-personal accounts are not permitted. 
If you would like to invest with another person, or to make regular contributions rather than investing a lump sum, please call 03456 076180* to discuss your options.






Please read the important information below

Global Investment Centre has been created for individual investors who want to make lump sum investments themselves. You cannot make regular payments or joint applications in to the Global Investment Centre.
Investors should regularly review the funds they've chosen. That's why with Global Investment Centre you can see the current value of your investments, and track their performance, at a glance.
Once you've applied for the Global Investment Centre, you can open a Funds Portfolio in which to buy, sell and hold your investments. 
You can also apply for an ISA Funds Portfolio so you can hold your investments within a tax-efficient ISA.
The minimum initial investment is £100 for each class of fund shares for each portfolio. The minimum additional investment is also £100. 
Online trades through the Global Investment Centre are limited to £99,999. If you would like to place a trade of £100,000 or more, you may do so by phone – please call us on 03456 076180**.




